name: Request for Canadian plant records
note:
On behalf of Dr. Cota-Sanchez, the Curator of the W.P. Fraser Herbarium (SASK), we request a listing of records (current and historical) of your Canadian herbarium holdings of the following plants:
Droseraceae: Drosera anglica, D. liinearis, D. rotundifolia
Lentibulariaceae: Pinguicula villosa, P. vulgaris, Utricula cornuta, U. intermedia, U. minor, U. macrohiza
Sarracenuaceae: Sarracenia purpurea

Some of you have already sent us your Saskatchewan records. Dr. Cota-Sanchez has decided to expand his research project to include all Canadian records of the above plants. We would appreciate it if you could provide the label data for your specimens on an Excel spreadsheet including the following information:
- your accession number
- locality information
- habitat information
- date collected
- collector name(s) and number
Or, if it is more convenient, photocopies or scanned images of the label data can be sent.
